<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="557" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,506,1434]" box="[151,989,506,531]" pageId="2" pageNumber="557">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,506,531]" pageId="2" pageNumber="557">Description.</emphasis>
Length (including wings): male 6.0 mm, female 
<quantity box="[847,984,506,531]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.45" metricValueMax="6.7" metricValueMin="6.2" pageId="2" pageNumber="557" unit="mm" value="6.45" valueMax="6.7" valueMin="6.2">6.2–6.7 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,506,1434]" pageId="2" pageNumber="557">
Crown stramineous; face mainly yellowish; frontoclypeus brownish basally, with dark brown tinge on median line, lateral margin brown; anteclypeus dark brown, yellowish brown anteriorly; lateral frontal sutures terminating at pair of black spots ventromesad of ocelli; ocelli transparent; gena and lora ochraceous, with gray stripes. Pronotum yellowish anteriorly and brown basally, with brown stripes (
<figureCitation box="[937,1010,650,675]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1726,1748]" captionTargetBox="[156,1436,199,1702]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1705]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Flexocerus sinuatus sp. nov. A, habitus of male, dorsal view; B, habitus of male, lateral view; C, head and thorax of male, dorsal view; D, face of male; E, head and thorax of female, dorsal view; F, face of female; G, habitus of female, dorsal view; H, habitus of female, lateral view. Idioceroides petaliformis sp. nov. I, habitus, dorsal view; J, habitus, lateral view; K, head and thorax, dorsal view; L, face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/245573/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="557">
Figs. 
<number box="[1000,1010,651,675]" pageId="2" pageNumber="557" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
C–D). Forewing brownish, veins dark brown. Scutellum yellowish, basal triangles and disc black. Mesoepimeron and legs ochraceous, hind leg macrosetae brownish (
<figureCitation box="[403,467,722,747]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1726,1748]" captionTargetBox="[156,1436,199,1702]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1705]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Flexocerus sinuatus sp. nov. A, habitus of male, dorsal view; B, habitus of male, lateral view; C, head and thorax of male, dorsal view; D, face of male; E, head and thorax of female, dorsal view; F, face of female; G, habitus of female, dorsal view; H, habitus of female, lateral view. Idioceroides petaliformis sp. nov. I, habitus, dorsal view; J, habitus, lateral view; K, head and thorax, dorsal view; L, face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/245573/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="557">
Fig. 
<number box="[456,467,723,747]" pageId="2" pageNumber="557" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
B).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,506,1434]" box="[199,1125,758,783]" pageId="2" pageNumber="557">Face with lateral frontal sutures straight; other characters as in generic description.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,506,1434]" pageId="2" pageNumber="557">
Male pygofer rectangular, caudal margin rounded, dorsal margin with apodeme; pygofer with dense short setae and concave on ventral margin subapically, inner surface with a finger-shaped process (
<figureCitation box="[1127,1193,830,855]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1726,1748]" captionTargetBox="[170,1411,216,1691]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1705]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Flexocerus sinuatus sp. nov. A, male pygofer, anal tube and subgenital plate, lateral view; B, valve; C, connective, lateral view; D, connective, ventral view; E, aedeagus, lateral view; F, aedeagus, ventral view; G, style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/245575/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="557">
Fig. 
<number box="[1179,1193,831,855]" pageId="2" pageNumber="557" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
A). Valve with caudal margin convex in middle (
<figureCitation box="[447,513,866,891]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1726,1748]" captionTargetBox="[170,1411,216,1691]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1705]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Flexocerus sinuatus sp. nov. A, male pygofer, anal tube and subgenital plate, lateral view; B, valve; C, connective, lateral view; D, connective, ventral view; E, aedeagus, lateral view; F, aedeagus, ventral view; G, style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/245575/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="557">
Fig. 
<number box="[499,513,867,891]" pageId="2" pageNumber="557" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
B). Subgenital plate narrow and elongate, with dense long fine setae on dorsal and ventral margin, fine setae on lateral surface. Style broad subapically, tapering apically, apex pointed, with more than 
<number box="[209,237,939,963]" pageId="2" pageNumber="557" value="20.0">20</number>
teeth on apical half ventral margin, few short setae on lateral surface in middle (
<figureCitation box="[1177,1245,938,963]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1726,1748]" captionTargetBox="[170,1411,216,1691]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1705]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Flexocerus sinuatus sp. nov. A, male pygofer, anal tube and subgenital plate, lateral view; B, valve; C, connective, lateral view; D, connective, ventral view; E, aedeagus, lateral view; F, aedeagus, ventral view; G, style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/245575/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="557">
Fig. 
<number box="[1231,1245,939,963]" pageId="2" pageNumber="557" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
G). Aedeagus Sshaped, with 
<number box="[304,318,975,999]" pageId="2" pageNumber="557" value="3.0">3</number>
processes, pair of long ventral subapical processes medially above gonopore and shorter process medially below gonopore; dorsal apodeme with pair of winglike apical extensions in ventral view; gonopore subapical (
<figureCitation box="[272,348,1046,1071]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1726,1748]" captionTargetBox="[170,1411,216,1691]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1705]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Flexocerus sinuatus sp. nov. A, male pygofer, anal tube and subgenital plate, lateral view; B, valve; C, connective, lateral view; D, connective, ventral view; E, aedeagus, lateral view; F, aedeagus, ventral view; G, style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/245575/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="557">
Figs. 
<number box="[335,348,1047,1071]" pageId="2" pageNumber="557" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
E–F).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,506,1434]" pageId="2" pageNumber="557">
Female 
<number box="[288,302,1086,1109]" pageId="2" pageNumber="557" value="7.0">7</number>
th sternum shorter than wide, rectangular, apical margin with a triangular concavity in middle. Second valvulae curved dorsally, with sixteen dorsal teeth; first valvulae sculpture strigate, apex compressed and pointed (
<figureCitation box="[159,229,1157,1182]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1221,1243]" captionTargetBox="[173,1413,197,1183]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[162,1424,193,1199]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Flexocerus sinuatus sp. nov. A, first valvulae; B, second valvulae; C, apex of first valvulae; D, female genitalia, ventral view; E, apex of second valvulae; F, fore femur, anterior view; G, fore tibia, anterior view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/245574/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="557">
Fig. 
<number box="[212,229,1158,1182]" pageId="2" pageNumber="557" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,962,1193,1218]" pageId="2" pageNumber="557" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,506,1434]" box="[199,962,1193,1218]" pageId="2" pageNumber="557">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1193,1218]" pageId="2" pageNumber="557">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet refers to the aedeagal shaft sinuate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
