<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="557" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,506,1434]" pageId="2" pageNumber="557">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1337,1362]" pageId="2" pageNumber="557">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Li" authorityName="Li" box="[607,752,1337,1362]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Flexocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="557" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="citrinus">
<emphasis box="[607,720,1338,1361]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="557">F. citrinus</emphasis>
Li
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Kuoh &amp; Fang" authorityName="Kuoh &amp; Fang" box="[807,1098,1337,1362]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Flexocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="557" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flexureus">
<emphasis box="[807,936,1337,1362]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="557">F. flexureus</emphasis>
Kuoh &amp; Fang
</taxonomicName>
in face color, but differs from the latter in having the pygofer with a finger-shaped process on the inner surface ventrally, and the aedeagus with 
<number box="[1422,1436,1374,1398]" pageId="2" pageNumber="557" value="3.0">3</number>
processes on the ventral surface.
</paragraph>
